            Because as the motor lifts the load, friction in its bearings etc generates heat. By the law of entropy, this heat energy must be dissipated, so it must dissipate into the thermal store of the surroundings as the load is lifted. As the motor lifts the load, sound may also be generated. Sound waves move out from the motor and hit objects in the surroundings, which absorb and eventually convert the sound into thermal energy. In general, waste energy in the form of radiation generally gets converted into thermal energy, which is dissipated into the thermal store of the surroundings.
