9.
    a.
        i.
            F = ma; 41000 = 830a; a = 41000/830 = 49.3975903614 ~= 50
        ii.
            26^2 = 72^2 + (-50) * 2 * s
            s = (26^2 - 72^2)/(-50 * 2)
            = 45.08m
            ~= 45.1m
    b.
        Energy must always be conserved. Kinetic energy is 1/2 * mass * velocity^2. When the car slows down, velocity decreases, since mass is constant. This would lower the total energy of the car/system, so therefore energy must increase in some other place. Since energy is proportional to the square of velocity, there is a lot of energy which needs to be taken away from the kinetic store and put into another store. The main store is thermal, of the brakes. Hence, the brakes must get very hot, since there is a lot of kinetic energy that needs to be converted into thermal energy.
    c.
        Insulators do not conduct heat well. Several layers of insulating material may mean that there is less contact between the layers, so less heat transfer by conduction occurs; in general, heat is conducted at a much slower rate from the tyres to the mechanic's hands, meaning that the mechanic must touch the tyres for a much longer time to burn their hands as opposed to if there was no insulationl
